<br />
<br />What would happen then if any of us would become rich ? Would this help people to complete their NES homebrew projects ? I think it doesn't make sense.
<br />You'd just have no problem with buying rare cartridge with a rare board on eBay for $200 (to make sure nobody will put a higher price) and then destroy it to input your own game, wich is kinda stupid in some way.
<br />
<br />Oh yeah, if any would become REALLY rich he could give classes to teach how to programm to the NES and then pay them as full time employees to people that would already got some formation on how to programm games. That could help, but that would require getting ridiculously rich and then ridiculously waste that money. If someone would do that, he would definitely do it for a modern gaming system or PCs, so that more people would be actually intereseted in his games and he could do a much better buisness (anyway I don't programm games for buisness myself).</div>

					
