						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Meeting modern expectations on antique platform is a pretty interesting challenge, I know from designing (but far from fully programming) a game I was working on. </div>
<br />Well, I'm unsure what exactly the modern exeptations are today. I really don't mind if people that say "anything that is in 2D sucks" aren't interested in my games. However, I'd still like not to have only hardcore oldscool gamers interested. I'd like to make everyone understand that if a game was good 15 years ago it is still good today, and that if graphics were great 20 years ago they are still great today. I consider the large majority of 3D games have worse graphics than 2D games due to the atrocious look of sharped polygons, wich never happens with pixels drawn carefully by hand (even with low resolusion). Only the very last recent 3D games can graphically compete with the SNES games with good graphics now.
<br />
<br />And you mean you would build your own famiclones with much more accurate hardware (Nintendulator in the form of a console ?). That would be great, but yeah, unresonable.</div>

					
